    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-12-05</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-02-08T22:05:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Reforming an Entitlement through Premium Adjustments based on Income Resources (REPAIR) Act of 2007 - Amends part D (Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program) of title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to require an income-related reduction in the part D premium subsidy.</p> <p> Declares that, in the case of an individual whose modified adjusted gross income exceeds a certain applicable threshold amount for a month after December 2008, the monthly amount of the part D premium subsidy shall be reduced (and the monthly beneficiary premium shall be increased) by the monthly adjustment amount determined according to a specified formula.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Reforming an Entitlement through Premium Adjustments based on Income Resources (REPAIR) Act of 2007</title>
